# Component Creation Guidelines

## Before Creating a New Component

1. **Check if it exists**: Look in `lib/components.tsx` or `component-registry.json`
2. **Check if composable**: Can existing components be combined?
3. **Only create new if necessary**

## Component Structure

Every component must follow this pattern:

```tsx
// In lib/components.tsx

export function MyComponent({
  title = "Default",
  variant = "default",
  size = "md",
  disabled = false,
  onClick,
}: {
  title?: string;
  variant?: "default" | "primary" | "danger";
  size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
  disabled?: boolean;
  onClick?: () => void;
}) {
  const c = useColors();
  
  return (
    <div
      style={{
        padding: spacing[4],
        borderRadius: radius.lg,
        backgroundColor: c.background.section,
      }}
      onClick={disabled ? undefined : onClick}
    >
      <span style={{
        fontSize: typography.fontSize.base,
        fontWeight: typography.fontWeight.medium,
        color: c.text.default,
      }}>
        {title}
      </span>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Required Patterns

### 1. Use TypeScript Props

```tsx
// ✅ Correct - inline types with defaults
function Component({
  prop1 = "default",
  prop2 = false,
}: {
  prop1?: string;
  prop2?: boolean;
}) { }

// ❌ Avoid - separate interface (unless complex)
interface Props { }
```

### 2. Always Use Design Tokens

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
style={{
  padding: spacing[4],
  backgroundColor: c.background.section,
}}

// ❌ Wrong
style={{
  padding: 16,
  backgroundColor: "#31333A",
}}
```

### 3. Use useColors() Hook

```tsx
function Component() {
  const c = useColors();  // Always first line
  
  return (
    <div style={{ color: c.text.default }}>
      ...
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 4. Provide Sensible Defaults

```tsx
// ✅ All props have defaults
function Button({
  label = "Button",
  variant = "primary",
  size = "md",
  disabled = false,
}: { ... })

// ❌ No defaults
function Button({ label, variant }: { ... })
```

### 5. Interactive States

```tsx
const [isHovered, setIsHovered] = useState(false);
const [isPressed, setIsPressed] = useState(false);

<div
  style={{
    backgroundColor: isPressed 
      ? c.background.pressed 
      : isHovered 
        ? c.background.hover 
        : c.background.section,
    transition: "background-color 150ms ease",
  }}
  onMouseEnter={() => setIsHovered(true)}
  onMouseLeave={() => setIsHovered(false)}
  onMouseDown={() => setIsPressed(true)}
  onMouseUp={() => setIsPressed(false)}
>
```

## Component Variants

Use union types for variants:

```tsx
const variantStyles = {
  primary: {
    backgroundColor: c.primary.default,
    color: c.primary.inverse,
  },
  secondary: {
    backgroundColor: c.background.section,
    color: c.text.default,
  },
  danger: {
    backgroundColor: c.error.default,
    color: c.error.inverse,
  },
};

return (
  <button style={variantStyles[variant]}>
    {label}
  </button>
);
```

## Component Registration

After creating a component, add it to `componentRegistry`:

```tsx
export const componentRegistry: ComponentEntry[] = [
  // ... existing
  {
    name: "MyComponent",
    slug: "my-component",
    description: "Brief description",
    category: "Category",
    component: MyComponent,
    defaultProps: {
      title: "Default",
      variant: "default",
    },
    props: [
      { name: "title", type: "string", defaultValue: "Default" },
      { name: "variant", type: "select", options: ["default", "primary", "danger"], defaultValue: "default" },
    ],
  },
];
```

## Checklist

- [ ] Uses `useColors()` for all colors
- [ ] Uses design tokens for spacing/radius/typography
- [ ] All props have default values
- [ ] Props use TypeScript types
- [ ] Follows existing naming conventions
- [ ] Added to `componentRegistry`
- [ ] Updated `component-registry.json`
